CAPE TOWN The Maitland Flying Squad arrested three suspects for the illegal possession of drugs and precious metals, Western Cape police said on Wednesday.The officers were tipped off about an unlicensed firearm in a house in Gugulethu.After searching the premises, police found 268 mandrax tablets, a "considerable" amount of money, and presumed gold consisting of two bars, three packets of balls, and 273 coins on Tuesday.READ: Understanding Judge Davis's dagga judgmentPolice spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Andr Traut, said: The value of these items is yet to be determined as well as the authenticity thereof. The firearm was not found. Two women, aged 64 and 57, and man aged 28 were arrested and will appear in the Wynberg Magistrate's Court on Thursday.African News Agency